{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351545654,"sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fd1e8200138Tb4nroISeO0f","sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","messageID":"msg_ce3fd1654001TeSWEuIRnyHwPR","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_017RwD8xRMiN9AdTbq9pGgqN","tool":"bash","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"which portless 2>/dev/null; command -v portless 2>/dev/null; type portless 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; bun x portless --help 2>&1 | head -30 || true; echo \"---\"; npm info portless 2>&1 | head -20 || true","description":"Check if portless is available","timeout":15000},"output":"portless not found\nportless not found\n---\nResolving dependencies\nResolved, downloaded and extracted [6]\nSaved lockfile\n\nportless - Replace port numbers with stable, named .localhost URLs. For humans and agents.\n\nEliminates port conflicts, memorizing port numbers, and cookie/storage\nclashes by giving each dev server a stable .localhost URL.\n\nInstall:\n  npm install -g portless\n  Do NOT add portless as a project dependency.\n\nUsage:\n  portless proxy start             Start the proxy (background daemon)\n  portless proxy start --https     Start with HTTP/2 + TLS (auto-generates certs)\n  portless proxy start -p 80       Start on port 80 (requires sudo)\n  portless proxy stop              Stop the proxy\n  portless <name> <cmd>            Run your app through the proxy\n  portless run <cmd>               Infer name from project, run through proxy\n  portless get <name>              Print URL for a service (for cross-service refs)\n  portless alias <name> <port>     Register a static route (e.g. for Docker)\n  portless alias --remove <name>   Remove a static route\n  portless list                    Show active routes\n  portless trust                   Add local CA to system trust store\n  portless hosts sync              Add routes to /etc/hosts (fixes Safari)\n  portless hosts clean             Remove portless entries from /etc/hosts\