{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351549327,"sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fd32c1001lmZouRkZOKlX4H","sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","messageID":"msg_ce3fd2b44001PyxVcH8aruOHlq","type":"text","text":"Now I understand portless. It's a tool that replaces port numbers with stable `.localhost` URLs, preventing port collisions. Let me understand the key integration points:","time":{"start":1773351549327,"end":1773351549327}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351549578,"sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fd36d70013u3VAGqafGw1Gt","sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","messageID":"msg_ce3fd2b44001PyxVcH8aruOHlq","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01WieaGRxC9jVgCCeeZJv32D","tool":"bash","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"bun x portless --help 2>&1; echo \"===\"; bun x portless proxy --help 2>&1 || true","description":"Get portless detailed help","timeout":15000},"output":"\nportless - Replace port numbers with stable, named .localhost URLs. For humans and agents.\n\nEliminates port conflicts, memorizing port numbers, and cookie/storage\nclashes by giving each dev server a stable .localhost URL.\n\nInstall:\n  npm install -g portless\n  Do NOT add portless as a project dependency.\n\nUsage:\n  portless proxy start             Start the proxy (background daemon)\n  portless proxy start --https     Start with HTTP/2 + TLS (auto-generates certs)\n  portless proxy start -p 80       Start on port 80 (requires sudo)\n  portless proxy stop              Stop the proxy\n  portless <name> <cmd>            Run your app through the proxy\n  portless run <cmd>               Infer name from project, run through proxy\n  portless get <name>              Print URL for a service (for cross-service refs)\n  portless alias <name> <port>     Register a static route (e.g. for Docker)\n  portless alias --remove <name>   Remove a static route\n  portless list                    Show active routes\n  portless trust                   Add local CA to system trust store\n  portless hosts sync              Add routes to /etc/hosts (fixes Safari)\n  portless hosts clean             Remove portless entries from /etc/hosts\n\nExamples:\n  portless proxy start                # Start proxy on port 1355\n  portless proxy start --https        # Start with HTTPS/2 (faster page loads)\n  portless myapp next dev             # -> http://myapp.localhost:1355\n  portless myapp vite dev             # -> http://myapp.localhost:1355\n  portless api.myapp pnpm start       # -> http://api.myapp.localhost:1355\n  portless run next dev               # -> http://<project>.localhost:1355\n  portless run next dev               # in worktree -> http://<worktree>.<project>.localhost:1355\n  portless get backend                 # -> http://backend.localhost:1355 (for cross-service refs)\n  # Wildcard subdomains: tenant.myapp.localhost also routes to myapp\n\nIn package.json:\n  {\n    \"scripts\": {\n      \"dev\": \"portless run next dev\"\n    }\n  }\n\nHow it works:\n  1. Start the proxy once (listens on port 1355 by default, no sudo needed)\n  2. Run your apps - they auto-start the proxy and register automatically\n     (apps get a random port in the 4000-4999 range via PORT)\n  3. Access via http://<name>.localhost:1355\n  4. .localhost domains auto-resolve to 127.0.0.1\n  5. Frameworks that ignore PORT (Vite, Astro, React Router, Angular,\n     Expo, React Native) get --port and --host flags injected automatically\n\nHTTP/2 + HTTPS:\n  Use --https for HTTP/2 multiplexing (faster dev server page loads).\n  On first use, portless generates a local CA and adds it to your\n  system trust store. No browser warnings. No sudo required on macOS.\n\nOptions:\n  run [--name <name>] <cmd>      Infer project name (or override with --name)\n                                Adds worktree prefix in git worktrees\n  -p, --port <number>           Port for the proxy to listen on (default: 1355)\n                                Ports < 1024 require sudo\n  --https                       Enable HTTP/2 + TLS with auto-generated certs\n  --cert <path>                 Use a custom TLS certificate (implies --https)\n  --key <path>                  Use a custom TLS private key (implies --https)\n  --no-tls                      Disable HTTPS (overrides PORTLESS_HTTPS)\n  --foreground                  Run proxy in foreground (for debugging)\n  --tld <tld>                   Use a custom TLD instead of .localhost (e.g. test, dev)\n  --app-port <number>           Use a fixed port for the app (skip auto-assignment)\n  --force                       Override an existing route registered by another process\n  --name <name>                 Use <name> as the app name (bypasses subcommand dispatch)\n  --                            Stop flag parsing; everything after is passed to the child\n\nEnvironment variables:\n  PORTLESS_PORT=<number>        Override the default proxy port (e.g. in .bashrc)\n  PORTLESS_APP_PORT=<number>    Use a fixed port for the app (same as --app-port)\n  PORTLESS_HTTPS=1              Always enable HTTPS (set in .bashrc / .zshrc)\n  PORTLESS_TLD=<tld>            Use a custom TLD (e.g. test, dev; default: localhost)\n  PORTLESS_SYNC_HOSTS=1         Auto-sync /etc/hosts (auto-enabled for custom TLDs)\n  PORTLESS_STATE_DIR=<path>     Override the state directory\n  PORTLESS=0                    Run command directly without proxy\n\nChild process environment:\n  PORT                          Ephemeral port the child should listen on\n  HOST                          Always 127.0.0.1\n  PORTLESS_URL                  Public URL of the app (e.g. http://myapp.localhost:1355)\n\nSafari / DNS:\n  .localhost subdomains auto-resolve in Chrome, Firefox, and Edge.\n  Safari relies on the system DNS resolver, which may not handle them.\n  Auto-syncs /etc/hosts for custom TLDs (e.g. --tld test). For .localhost,\n  set PORTLESS_SYNC_HOSTS=1 to enable. To manually sync:\n    sudo portless hosts sync\n  Clean up later with:\n    sudo portless hosts clean\n\nSkip portless:\n  PORTLESS=0 pnpm dev           # Runs command directly without proxy\n\nReserved names:\n  run, get, alias, hosts, list, trust, proxy are subcommands and cannot\n  be used as app names directly. Use \"portless run\" to infer the name,\n  or \"portless --name <name>\" to force any name including reserved ones.\n\n===\n\nportless proxy - Manage the portless proxy server.\n\nUsage:\n  portless proxy start                Start the proxy (daemon)\n  portless proxy start --https        Start with HTTP/2 + TLS\n  portless proxy start --foreground   Start in foreground (for debugging)\n  portless proxy start -p 80          Start on port 80 (requires sudo)\n  portless proxy start --tld test     Use .test instead of .localhost\n  portless proxy stop                 Stop the proxy\n\n","title":"Get portless detailed help","metadata":{"output":"\nportless - Replace port numbers with stable, named .localhost URLs. For humans and agents.\n\nEliminates port conflicts, memorizing port numbers, and cookie/storage\nclashes by giving each dev server a stable .localhost URL.\n\nInstall:\n  npm install -g portless\n  Do NOT add portless as a project dependency.\n\nUsage:\n  portless proxy start             Start the proxy (background daemon)\n  portless proxy start --https     Start with HTTP/2 + TLS (auto-generates certs)\n  portless proxy start -p 80       Start on port 80 (requires sudo)\n  portless proxy stop              Stop the proxy\n  portless <name> <cmd>            Run your app through the proxy\n  portless run <cmd>               Infer name from project, run through proxy\n  portless get <name>              Print URL for a service (for cross-service refs)\n  portless alias <name> <port>     Register a static route (e.g. for Docker)\n  portless alias --remove <name>   Remove a static route\n  portless list                    Show active routes\n  portless trust                   Add local CA to system trust store\n  portless hosts sync              Add routes to /etc/hosts (fixes Safari)\n  portless hosts clean             Remove portless entries from /etc/hosts\n\nExamples:\n  portless proxy start                # Start proxy on port 1355\n  portless proxy start --https        # Start with HTTPS/2 (faster page loads)\n  portless myapp next dev             # -> http://myapp.localhost:1355\n  portless myapp vite dev             # -> http://myapp.localhost:1355\n  portless api.myapp pnpm start       # -> http://api.myapp.localhost:1355\n  portless run next dev               # -> http://<project>.localhost:1355\n  portless run next dev               # in worktree -> http://<worktree>.<project>.localhost:1355\n  portless get backend                 # -> http://backend.localhost:1355 (for cross-service refs)\n  # Wildcard subdomains: tenant.myapp.localhost also routes to myapp\n\nIn package.json:\n  {\n    \"scripts\": {\n      \"dev\": \"portless run next dev\"\n    }\n  }\n\nHow it works:\n  1. Start the proxy once (listens on port 1355 by default, no sudo needed)\n  2. Run your apps - they auto-start the proxy and register automatically\n     (apps get a random port in the 4000-4999 range via PORT)\n  3. Access via http://<name>.localhost:1355\n  4. .localhost domains auto-resolve to 127.0.0.1\n  5. Frameworks that ignore PORT (Vite, Astro, React Router, Angular,\n     Expo, React Native) get --port and --host flags injected automatically\n\nHTTP/2 + HTTPS:\n  Use --https for HTTP/2 multiplexing (faster dev server page loads).\n  On first use, portless generates a local CA and adds it to your\n  system trust store. No browser warnings. No sudo required on macOS.\n\nOptions:\n  run [--name <name>] <cmd>      Infer project name (or override with --name)\n                                Adds worktree prefix in git worktrees\n  -p, --port <number>           Port for the proxy to listen on (default: 1355)\n                                Ports < 1024 require sudo\n  --https                       Enable HTTP/2 + TLS with auto-generated certs\n  --cert <path>                 Use a custom TLS certificate (implies --https)\n  --key <path>                  Use a custom TLS private key (implies --https)\n  --no-tls                      Disable HTTPS (overrides PORTLESS_HTTPS)\n  --foreground                  Run proxy in foreground (for debugging)\n  --tld <tld>                   Use a custom TLD instead of .localhost (e.g. test, dev)\n  --app-port <number>           Use a fixed port for the app (skip auto-assignment)\n  --force                       Override an existing route registered by another process\n  --name <name>                 Use <name> as the app name (bypasses subcommand dispatch)\n  --                            Stop flag parsing; everything after is passed to the child\n\nEnvironment variables:\n  PORTLESS_PORT=<number>        Override the default proxy port (e.g. in .bashrc)\n  PORTLESS_APP_PORT=<number>    Use a fixed port for the app (same as --app-port)\n  PORTLESS_HTTPS=1              Always enable HTTPS (set in .bashrc / .zshrc)\n  PORTLESS_TLD=<tld>            Use a custom TLD (e.g. test, dev; default: localhost)\n  PORTLESS_SYNC_HOSTS=1         Auto-sync /etc/hosts (auto-enabled for custom TLDs)\n  PORTLESS_STATE_DIR=<path>     Override the state directory\n  PORTLESS=0                    Run command directly without proxy\n\nChild process environment:\n  PORT                          Ephemeral port the child should listen on\n  HOST                          Always 127.0.0.1\n  PORTLESS_URL                  Public URL of the app (e.g. http://myapp.localhost:1355)\n\nSafari / DNS:\n  .localhost subdomains auto-resolve in Chrome, Firefox, and Edge.\n  Safari relies on the system DNS resolver, which may not handle them.\n  Auto-syncs /etc/hosts for custom TLDs (e.g. --tld test). For .localhost,\n  set PORTLESS_SYNC_HOSTS=1 to enable. To manually sync:\n    sudo portless hosts sync\n  Clean up later with:\n    sudo portless hosts clean\n\nSkip portless:\n  PORTLESS=0 pnpm dev           # Runs command directly without proxy\n\nReserved names:\n  run, get, alias, hosts, list, trust, proxy are subcommands and cannot\n  be used as app names directly. Use \"portless run\" to infer the name,\n  or \"portless --name <name>\" to force any name including reserved ones.\n\n===\n\nportless proxy - Manage the portless proxy server.\n\nUsage:\n  portless proxy start                Start the proxy (daemon)\n  portless proxy start --https        Start with HTTP/2 + TLS\n  portless proxy start --foreground   Start in foreground (for debugging)\n  portless proxy start -p 80          Start on port 80 (requires sudo)\n  portless proxy start --tld test     Use .test instead of .localhost\n  portless proxy stop                 Stop the proxy\n\n","exit":0,"description":"Get portless detailed help","truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773351549316,"end":1773351549577}}}}
