{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351558390,"sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fd4443002WWWZM4o6FOEIT0","sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","messageID":"msg_ce3fd3a990012Ll5ykpm8jU7oI","type":"text","text":"This is extremely useful. The key insight is that `portless run <cmd>` automatically:\n1. Detects if running in a git worktree and adds a worktree prefix\n2. Sets `PORT` env var to an ephemeral port\n3. Sets `PORTLESS_URL` env var to the stable URL\n4. Injects `--port` and `--host` flags for common frameworks\n\nNow I have a complete understanding. Let me create my plan:","time":{"start":1773351558389,"end":1773351558389}}}
