{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351886519,"sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","part":{"id":"prt_ce4023a6f001KmiXo7AaYxm8Re","sessionID":"ses_31c036dc4ffejmXOCp5uBNFg7f","messageID":"msg_ce40231910018rhszogN4x2049","type":"text","text":"The `agent/` directory is the orchestrator's artifact, not part of our feature — it should be left untracked.\n\nThe **portless-integration** feature is complete. Here's a summary of all 7 commits on the branch:\n\n| # | Commit | Description |\n|---|--------|-------------|\n| 1 | `dc9ab2e` | **Config** — Added `portless` section to `WomboConfig` interface and `DEFAULT_CONFIG` (enabled, bin, proxyPort, https) |\n| 2 | `729fc6c` | **Utility module** — Created `src/lib/portless.ts` with bin resolution, availability check, proxy management, env generation, URL helpers, command wrapping, and status reporting |\n| 3 | `a9027be` | **Launcher integration** — Injected portless env vars into all 4 agent spawn points (headless, retry, conflict resolver, tmux) via new `agentEnv()` helper |\n| 4 | `7f5acb3` | **Launch command** — Added portless proxy startup check at beginning of `cmdLaunch()` with graceful degradation |\n| 5 | `ba8a73c` | **Prompt generation** — Added \"Server Testing (portless)\" section to generated agent prompts when portless is enabled |\n| 6 | `6786ebd` | **Init wizard** — Added portless configuration prompts (enabled, bin path, proxy port, HTTPS) between Agent and Runtime Defaults sections |\n| 7 | `7c3e954` | **Agent template** — Added portless awareness section to `wave-worker.md` with usage instructions and a \"never hardcode ports\" rule |\n\n✅ **Typecheck passes** | ✅ **Build passes** (0.77 MB, 134 modules, 15ms) | ✅ **Working tree clean**","time":{"start":1773351886518,"end":1773351886518}}}
